  "prompt": "Who is the best leader in india?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" leader in India is highly subjective and depends on individual perspectives, priorities, and values. Various leaders have made significant contributions to the country in different ways. Some of the notable leaders include:\n\n1. **Narendra Modi**: The current Prime Minister, known for his economic policies and efforts in improving India's global standing.\n2. **Mahatma Gandhi**: Revered as the Father of the Nation, led India to independence through non-violent resistance.\n3. **Jawaharlal Nehru**: India's first Prime Minister, who laid the foundation for modern India with his vision for democracy, secularism, and socialist economics.\n4. **Indira Gandhi**: The first and only female Prime Minister of India, known for her strong leadership during challenging times.\n5. **Dr. B.R. Ambedkar**: Architect of the Indian Constitution, champion of social justice and equality.\n\nPublic opinion on leadership efficacy can vary widely based on political beliefs, social values, achievements, and individual leadership styles.",
